Hello, I'm Afia Adiba Hafsa, a high school student, and my friend (Team mate) Taskin Tahira Ridma  from Islamic University Of Technology from Civil & Environmental Engineering Dept. 
Our backgrounds in environmental systems taught us to see the bigger picture: infrastructure means nothing if communities can't sustain themselves. We've spent time in rural areas understanding challenges firsthand, not from textbooks. That's where we realized the gap wasn't just technical it was access, literacy, and trust.
We're building solutions that respect users' intelligence while removing complexity. Our approach: make powerful tools feel simple, speak people's language (literally), and prove value immediately. No lengthy onboarding, no steep learning curves just tools that work when you need them.

Our vision isn't about disruption; it's about enablement. We're creating systems where technology amplifies human capability without replacing human wisdom. Where traditional knowledge meets modern tools.

Our north star: If our solution disappeared tomorrow, would people notice? If the answer isn't "absolutely," we haven't built the right thing yet.
Team Coconut Crew, just as the name suggests, we bring fresh and refreshing ideas to life that no one has ever done.

NextGen Commerce Intelligence (NGCI) is a Bangladesh-based innovation team focused on building the future of AI-driven digital commerce. Our mission is to bring enterprise-grade market intelligence to every micro-merchant, SME, and online seller — making advanced analytics accessible, affordable, and fully localized for Bangladesh and emerging markets.

We believe that the next decade of economic growth in South Asia will be shaped by AI-first commerce. Our team aims to empower millions of small businesses with tools that analyze demand, optimize pricing, and automate inventory decisions in real time. NGCI combines expertise in machine learning, data engineering, multimodal AI, and product design to create solutions that are 10× smarter, simpler, and more inclusive.

Our project for MillionX — Intelligent Marketplace Optimizer — reimagines retail intelligence for Bangladesh and beyond. We are creating an AI engine that understands market signals, predicts trends, and delivers actionable recommendations through multilingual dashboards and conversational interfaces in Bangla & English. From Daraz sellers to Shopify entrepreneurs, our vision is to build a system that scales across South Asia, Africa, and LATAM.

At NGCI, we are committed to innovation, ethics, transparency, and impact. We believe AI can unlock new economic opportunities for SMEs and strengthen Bangladesh’s global digital footprint — helping shape a future where commerce is smarter, fairer, and accessible to everyone.

biography: We are Team Skill Stars_3N, a group of passionate builders committed to tackling the youth unemployment crisis in Bangladesh. We believe that financial barriers should never stop a student from becoming industry-ready. We are not just dreaming of a skilled nation; we are building the engine to power it.

We budding engineers blend academic rigor with an innovative approach to problem-solving to come up with solutions technically feasible, yet affordable and durable.

 We seek to make tomorrow safer for mothers and children in underprivileged communities. biography:
Founder & Lead Innovator: মৌ‌মিতা এহসান ঊষা
Country: Bangladesh
Project: MindMate – AI Mental Health Companion

About Mind Arch Innovators:
Mind Arch Innovators is a forward-thinking innovation initiative led solely by মৌ‌মিতা এহসান ঊষা, dedicated to leveraging technology for social impact. The initiative focuses on mental health, youth empowerment, and women’s well-being, combining artificial intelligence with human-centered design to create empathic, meaningful solutions.

Flagship Project – MindMate:
MindMate is an AI-driven mental health companion that goes beyond typical machine-controlled apps. It is designed not just to detect moods but to provide personalized, real-time emotional support for teenagers and young adults facing stress, anxiety, or emotional overwhelm. Unlike conventional AI tools, MindMate offers:

Daily mood check-ins and real-time mood detection

Secure, stigma-free conversational support

Personalized experiences like birthday gifts, surprise encouragements, and mood journaling

Professional help integration and crisis protection

Inclusive access for users of all socio-economic backgrounds

Methodology & Innovation:

Problem Statements & Abstract: Addresses the rising mental health challenges among youth, particularly in Bangladesh, where access to professional help is limited.

Prototype & Approach: Uses AI to sense emotions, track mood patterns, and deliver psychology-based micro-interventions.

Uniqueness: MindMate builds a digital emotional bond with users through caring interactions, personalized encouragement, and engagement activities — a feature unmatched in typical mental health apps.

Expected Results & Impact: Concept projections suggest 60% stress reduction, 75% motivation increase, 70% self-awareness growth, and 85% engagement with daily interactions.

Vision & Mission:
Mind Arch Innovators envisions a mega-project where MindMate becomes a core digital mental health ecosystem for Bangladesh and globally, supporting teenagers, young adults, and communities. The mission is to create safe, accessible, and stigma-free emotional support, fostering resilience, creativity, and personal growth while aligning with SDG 3 (Good Health & Well-Being), SDG 4 (Quality Education), and SDG 10 (Reduced Inequalities).

Achievements & Recognition:

Selected to represent Bangladesh at WYSII 2026, Bangkok through BYSIS Innovation Spark 1.0.

Featured in Grameen Kagoj, Channel i, Kaler Kontho, Dainik Jonokontho, and Jago News for social and technological impact.

Looking Ahead:
As a future startup, Mind Arch Innovators aims to scale MindMate into a national and global mental health solution, integrating schools, NGOs, clinics, and counselors. The focus remains on human-centered innovation, privacy, and inclusive emotional support, ensuring no user is left behind.

Mind Arch Innovators stands as a pioneering initiative where AI meets empathy, providing youth and young adults with tools to heal, grow, and thrive in a world increasingly challenged by stress and emotional overwhelm.

biography:
The vision of NextGenLearners is to transform traditional, curriculum-based education into an interactive, accountable, and learner-centric experience through the effective use of technology. The team envisions an education ecosystem where students develop strong conceptual understanding rather than relying on rote memorization, and where learning progress is measurable, transparent, and continuously improved.

Through the HomeSchool platform, NextGenLearners aims to bridge the gap between the national curriculum and modern digital learning practices. The project envisions a unified learning environment aligned with the NCTB syllabus that supports students from Class 6 to Class 12 with structured explanations, visual learning, regular assessments, and personalized feedback. HomeSchool is designed to empower students to learn independently while maintaining academic discipline and consistency.

A core element of the vision is active parental involvement. By providing parents with real-time insights into academic progress, performance trends, and study habits, the platform promotes shared responsibility and accountability in a student’s learning journey.

In the long term, NextGenLearners envisions HomeSchool as a scalable national learning companion—adopted by individual learners, families, and educational institutions—contributing to a more inclusive, data-driven, and digitally empowered education system in Bangladesh.

Next Billion Learners is a sister-founded initiative on a mission to democratize quality education across Bangladesh and beyond. Based in Khulna, we witnessed firsthand how traditional one-size-fits-all education leaves countless talented students behind. We believe every student learns differently, and technology can help us honor that difference.
Our flagship product, ShikkhaMitra, is an AI-powered adaptive tutor that combines Claude 4.5's advanced reasoning with deep understanding of Bangladeshi curriculum. The platform adapts in real-time to each student's learning pace, identifies weak areas automatically, and creates personalized study paths—all in both Bangla and English, with offline capability for low-bandwidth areas.
We're not just building an app; we're building the future of education. From the classrooms of Khulna to schools across Bangladesh, we're proving that AI-powered personalized education can scale to serve millions. Because the next billion learners deserve nothing less than education that adapts to them.

We are a passionate team from Chittagong University of Engineering & Technology (CUET), united by our love for innovation and problem-solving. Our mission is to explore ideas, tackle challenges, and turn them into impactful solutions that can inspire and make a difference.
